This paper discusses the relationships between humans and AI, which is a topic that falls under the category of Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). The paper proposes a framework called AI-Mediated Exchange Theory (AI-MET) to bridge the divides between different scholarly communities studying human-AI relationships, including social computing (cs.SI), machine learning (cs.AI), science and technology studies (cs.CY), and other social sciences (cs.CC). Therefore, these categories are also likely to be relevant to this paper.
